svg.text: Jamaicans migrate to USA, UK and Canada

text.tspan: So, where do Jamaicans move to? Predominately Jamaicans migrate to countries like the United
States, Canada, and the United Kingdom because they have established Jamaican communities
as well as stronger economies and higher wages.
Poverty is a big issue in Jamaicas economy and most unemployed
people are the ones facing the issue. When people can’t work and
afford things, this leads to financial problems, divorce, children losing
their education and health, hunger, fights and more which then can
lead to poverty.
To improve Jamaicas economy and increase young Jamaicans
employment opportunities the islands focus is on improving the
education and training provided to young people, with a greater focus
on vocational skills. Vocational college is a relevant platform to
respond to the demands of the modern workforce and will become a
driving force in propelling the effort to strengthen the economy.
Jamaica’s youth unemployment rate affects the islands ability to
achieve prosperity and see economic growth. Young Jamaicans are
struggling to find decent work to survive, improve their livelihoods and
overall improve the economy.
